OL,3,CHomeowner ignored planning laws and
OL,4,Cbuilt house 'too big and too tall'
OL,6,F"In addition, a masonry outbuilding
OL,7,Fhas been constructed on the land which
OL,8,Fdoes not have planning permission. The
OL,9,Ferection of the dwelling and
OL,10,Foutbuilding therefore amount to
OL,11,Funauthorised development."
OL,13,FThe council said the house was 'overly
OL,14,Fdominant within the plot' and was
OL,15,F'seriously detrimental to the visual
OL,16,Fand residential amenity' of those
OL,17,Fliving nearby.
OL,19,FThe authority ordered that to remedy
OL,20,Fthe planning breach the roof of the
OL,21,Fhouse needed to be reduced in height.
